  "text": "While modeling the second phase of tether development in the experiment of Shao et al. [CITATION_1] we have found that b eff ¼ 600 pN s mm À3 is the best fit to the experimental data of Shao et al. [CITATION_2] . It also fits well the experimental data of Heinrich et al. [CITATION_3] and Xu and Shao (12) , as discussed FIGURE 5 Modeled tether extension L, before (black) and after (gray in print/red online) crossover, for two cases (as indicated) of constant pulling force for the system, F sy , in the experiment of Shao et al. [CITATION_4] . The extension functions are overlaid on the experimental data of Shao et al. [CITATION_5] for two individual tethers. The functions are based on r c ¼ 4.5 mm and the other parameters as in Table 1 .",
